A former Limpopo principal is expected to appear at the Lenyenye Magistrate s Court on Tuesday(today) for allegedly raping a 15-year-old girl.It is reported that police in Tzaneen have arrested a 59-year-old man for raping a teenage girl at Lorraine Village in the Sekororo area last Wednesday.Police Lt-Colonel Moatshe&#8217; Ngoepe confirmed that the suspect handed himself.It is reported that he invited the girl to his house under the pretext that there was a message that she needed to receive. He allegedly took the girl to his house where he raped her.TNA Reporter&nbsp;&nbsp;